  dialogue:
  - What's the problem?
  - 'In fact, why is our food thrown out? '
  - '''t went bad.'
  - What?
  - Even the ones packed in cans started rottin'.
  - That shouldn't be possible.
  - Did you get some with faulty packaging?
  - T'don't matter now, lad. I went fishin' earlier te make up fer the loss...
  - ...'n' there wasn't nothin' out there.
  - Ye'll be goin' out tonight te try again.
  - Why can't you do it? You already went out before.
  - I lost me sea-legs, lad. I can only handle so much of the ocean waves these days.
  - Are you sure you can handle the lighthouse by yourself then?
  - Are ye questionin' me, lad?
  - I said ye're goin' fishin' so ye go out there 'n' fish.
  - Got that?
  - Yes, sir.
